    "A patch is deemed critical when the resulting change ∆P surpasses a predefined threshold significantly favoring the correct classification.",
    "These identified critical patches form the basis for constructing detailed causal graphs, providing insight into the internal decisionmaking pathways of the model.",
    "Attention SaliencyTo complement activation patching, we utilize attention saliency as an observational interpretability tool.",
    "Attention saliency clarifies which timesteps each attention head focuses on during prediction.",
    "Specifically, we extract raw attention weights A (h) ∈ R T ×T for each head h and average them across all query positions:S (h) t = 1 T T i=1 A (h) i,t,(2)where S(h) trepresents the average attention score for each timestep t. While attention saliency does not imply causation, it highlights potential candidate timesteps for targeted causal experiments."
